<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title><!-- Service Name --> — Olivia Arkema</title>
  <meta name="description" content="One-sentence summary of the service & outcome." />
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://oliviaarkema.com/services/service-slug" />

  <!-- Noto Serif (keep it simple) -->
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Noto+Serif:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

  <style>
    /* ===== Minimal design tokens ===== */
    :root{
      --bg:#faf7f2; --ink:#393831; --muted:#9e9383;
      --blue:#5f849c; --deep:#23424c; --wash:#dae4eb;
      --measure:72ch; --radius:14px;
    }

    /* ===== Base ===== */
    html,body{margin:0;padding:0}
    body{
      background:var(--bg);
      color:var(--ink);
      font:16px/1.75 'Noto Serif', serif;
      text-rendering:optimizeLegibility;
    }
    a{color:var(--deep); text-decoration:none}
    a:hover{text-decoration:underline}

    /* ===== Layout ===== */
    .wrap{max-width:960px; margin:0 auto; padding:0 20px}
    main{padding:3rem 0 4rem}
    header.site{padding:14px 0; border-bottom:1px solid #e8e4de; background:#fff}
    .brand{font-weight:700; color:var(--deep); font-size:20px}

    /* ===== Writing surface ===== */
    .letter{max-width:var(--measure); margin:0 auto}
    .lede{font-size:1.125rem; color:var(--muted); margin:.25rem 0 1rem}
    .meta{color:var(--muted); font-size:.95rem; margin:.25rem 0 1.5rem}

    /* Headings tuned for reading */
    h1,h2,h3{line-height:1.2; margin:0 0 .6rem}
    h1{font-size:clamp(28px,4vw,44px); color:var(--deep)}
    h2{font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,28px); color:var(--blue); margin-top:2.25rem}
    h3{font-size:clamp(18px,2.2vw,22px); color:var(--deep); margin-top:1.75rem}
    p{margin:0 0 1rem}

    /* Helpful writing blocks */
    .hr{height:1px; background:rgba(95,132,156,.25); margin:2rem 0}
    blockquote{
      margin:1.5rem 0; padding:.75rem 1rem;
      border-left:4px solid var(--blue); background:#fff; border-radius:8px;
      color:var(--deep)
    }
    .callout{
      background:#fff; border:2px solid var(--blue); border-radius:var(--radius);
      padding:1rem 1rem; margin:1.25rem 0;
    }
    figure{margin:1.25rem 0}
    figure img{display:block; width:100%; height:auto; border-radius:10px; border:2px solid var(--blue)}
    figcaption{font-size:.9rem; color:var(--muted); margin-top:.5rem; text-align:center}

    /* Lists & code (just in case) */
    ul,ol{padding-left:1.2rem; margin:0 0 1rem}
    code, pre{font-family:ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace}
    pre{background:#fff; border:1px solid #e8e4de; padding:1rem; border-radius:10px; overflow:auto}

    /* Simple CTA */
    .cta{
      display:inline-block; background:var(--blue); color:#fff;
      padding:.7rem 1rem; border-radius:10px; text-decoration:none
    }
    .cta:hover{filter:brightness(.95)}

    /* Optional: long-form two-column at very wide widths */
    @media (min-width: 1100px){
      .columns{column-count:2; column-gap:32px}
      .columns > *{break-inside:avoid}
    }

    footer.site{padding:28px 0; background:#393831; color:#9e9383}
    footer.site a{color:#9e9383}

    /* Sticky, simple site header */
    header.site{
      position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 10;
      background: #fff; border-bottom: 1px solid #e8e4de; /* already defined in your CSS */
    }
    
    /* Row + brand already look good; just layout */
    .site-row{ display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; gap:12px; }
    
    /* Desktop links */
    .site-links{ display:flex; gap:16px; flex-wrap:wrap; }
    
    /* Mobile toggle hidden on wide screens */
    .nav-toggle{ display:none; background:none; border:0; color:var(--muted); }
    
    /* Responsive behavior */
    @media (max-width: 760px){
      .nav-toggle{ display:inline-flex; }
      .site-links{
        display:none; position:absolute; right:20px; top:calc(100% + 8px);
        background:#fff; border:1px solid #e8e4de; border-radius:12px; padding:10px;
        box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(0,0,0,.08); width:calc(100% - 40px); max-width:440px;
        flex-direction:column; gap:10px;
      }
      .site-links.open{ display:flex; }
    }


  </style>
</head>
<body>
<header class="site">
  <div class="wrap site-row">
    <a class="brand" href="/">OA</a>

    <!-- Mobile toggle -->
    <button class="nav-toggle" aria-label="Open menu" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="site-menu">
      <svg width="26" height="26" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
        <path d="M4 7h16M4 12h16M4 17h16" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/>
      </svg>
    </button>

    <!-- Links -->
    <nav id="site-menu" class="site-links">
      <a href="/#home">Home</a>
      <a href="/#services">Services</a>
      <a href="/#clients">Clients</a>
      <a href="/#featuredwork">Featured Work</a>
      <a href="/#contact">Contact</a>
    </nav>
  </div>
</header>

  <!-- Spacer for fixed nav -->
  <div class="h-20 md:h-24"></div>

  <main>
    <article class="wrap letter">
      <!-- Title & lede -->
      <p class="meta">Signature Service</p>
      <h1>Service Name That Reads Like a Promise</h1>
      <p class="lede">A short, welcoming paragraph—set expectations, name the outcome, and invite the reader into a conversation.</p>

      <!-- Optional feature image -->
      <!-- <figure>
        <img src="/assets/service-hero.jpg" alt="Descriptive alt text" />
        <figcaption>Optional photo credit or context.</figcaption>
      </figure> -->

      <div class="hr"></div>

      <!-- Your letter / long-form content -->
      <section class="body">
        <!-- Add class="columns" to this section if you want two-column flow on very wide screens -->
        <!-- <section class="body columns"> -->
        <h2>Why this matters</h2>
        <p>Write like you talk. Share a belief, a tension, and a relief you provide. Keep paragraphs to 2–4 sentences for comfortable rhythm.</p>

        <h2>What I’ll do for you</h2>
        <p>Describe the approach in plain English. When helpful, use short lists:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Discovery and a plan you can see.</li>
          <li>Clear deliverables with dates.</li>
          <li>Lightweight check-ins and steady progress.</li>
        </ul>

        <blockquote>“Design-forward doesn’t have to be loud—clarity and calm are persuasive.”</blockquote>

        <h2>What you’ll need from me (and what I’ll need from you)</h2>
        <p>Set boundaries and expectations. Mention inputs, timelines, and decision points.</p>

        <div class="callout">
          <strong>Outcomes you can expect:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Measurable improvement (e.g., leads, conversions, or clarity).</li>
            <li>Artifacts you can reuse (templates, copy, assets).</li>
            <li>Confidence about next steps.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h2>Next step</h2>
        <p>If this sounds like what you need, email me a sentence about your goal and when you’d like to start.</p>
        <p><a class="cta" href="mailto:hello@oliviaarkema.com?subject=Project%20Inquiry">Email Olivia</a></p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>

  <footer class="site">
    <div class="wrap" style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap">
      <small>© <span id="year"></span> Olivia Arkema</small>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:14px"><a href="/privacy">Privacy</a><a href="/terms">Terms</a></div>
    </div>
  </footer>

  <script>
    document.getElementById('year').textContent = new Date().getFullYear();
  </script>
<script>
  const toggle = document.querySelector('.nav-toggle');
  const menu = document.getElementById('site-menu');
  if (toggle && menu){
    toggle.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const isOpen = menu.classList.toggle('open');
      toggle.setAttribute('aria-expanded', String(isOpen));
    });
  }
</script>
</body>
</html>
